'''Bath High School''' is a [[public high school]] located near [[Lima, Ohio]].  It is the only high school in the [[Bath Local School District]].

==Organizations==
School organizations at Bath include: [[School band|Band]], [[Symphonic Band]], [[Choir]], [[FCA]], [[National Honors Society]], [[Quiz Bowl]], [[Science Fair]], [[Math Counts]], [[SADD]], [[Science Olympiad]], [[Student Council]], and [[Yearbook]] editors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bathwildcats.org/HS/organization.html|title=Organizations}}</ref>

==Athletics==
The school's mascot is a wildcat for boys' sports, and a wildkitten for girls'.  They are members of the [[Western Buckeye League]].

===Ohio High School Athletic Association State Championships===
{{seealso|Ohio High School Athletic Association}}
* Boys [[Golf]] - 2005 <ref name="Ohio High School Athletic Association">{{cite web|url=http://www.ohsaa.org/|title=Ohio High School Athletic Association Web site|accessdate=2006-12-31|author=OHSAA}}</ref>
* Girls [[Basketball]] <U+2013> 1987 <ref name="Ohio High School Athletic Association">{{cite web|url=http://www.ohsaa.org/|title=Ohio High School Athletic Association Web site|accessdate=2006-12-31|author=OHSAA}}</ref>
* Girls [[Softball]] <U+2013> 2001 <ref name="Yappi Softball">{{cite web|url=http://www.yappi.com/softball/StateChamps.html|title=Yappi Sports Softball|accessdate=2007-02-12|author=Yappi}}</ref>

===Western Buckeye League Championships===
*[[Baseball]]: 1990, 1975, 1974, 1972, 1971<ref name="Western Buckeye League">{{cite web|url=http://www.wblsports.com/bathwildcats.html|title=Bath Wildcat WBL Championships|accessdate=2008-02-21|author=WBL}}</ref>

*Boys [[Basketball]]: 1971, 1970, 1969<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*Girls Basketball: 2009, 2008, 2006, 2001, 2000, 1999, 1998, 1996, 1994, 1987, 1986, 1985, 1983<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*[[American football]]: 1999, 1996, 1989, 1988, 1985, 1984, 1974, 1973<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*[[Golf]]: 2006, 2005, 2004, 1995, 1978, 1976, 1974, 1973, 1972, 1970, 1969, 1968, 1967, 1966<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*[[Softball]]: 2005, 2002, 2001, 1999, 1998, 1997, 1996, 1995, 1994, 1993, 1992, 1990, 1985, 1983<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*Boys [[Tennis]]: 1983, 1982<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*Boys [[Athletics (track and field)|Track]]: 1990, 1980, 1968<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />
*[[Volleyball]]: 1996, 1995, 1994, 1993, 1992, 1988<ref name="Western Buckeye League" />

==Recognition==
[[U.S. News & World Report]] awarded Bath High School a bronze award for their ''America's Best High Schools 2009 rankings''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usnews.com/directories/high-schools/index_html/state_id+OH/page_number+1/page_size+10/sort+alpha/name+/award+1+2+3+4/school_name+/county+/detail+more|title=Best High Schools 2009 Search|date=2008|publisher=U.S. News & World Report|accessdate=2008-12-21}}</ref>  They were the only high school in Allen County to be recognized.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usnews.com/forms/badges/high-schools/ohio/allen_county|title=America's Best High Schools 2009|date=2008|publisher=U.S. News & World Report|accessdate=2008-12-21}}</ref>

